<div style="float:left;margin:3px 20px 10px 0px;"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/852955ab40e0451456f0e84103a576f5?s=96&amp;d=&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='96'/></div>
<p>Start reading, what an ego !</p>
<p>&#8220;My book is the first serious attempt to bring together the seemingly disparate crises &#8230;&#8221;</p>
<p>Come on !</p>
<p>Just to cite one films that is so famous on the internet &#8220;money as debt&#8221; (2006), that says BEFORE the burst of the subprime that we are facing a global downturn due to resource crisis and that the two crisis are the same.</p>
<p>And that is only one exmaple that got fame on the net. How many people wrote one century ago about the future collapse of civilisation due to unsustainability of modern agriculture, human population and that linked all thses symptoms to a common problem ?</p>
<p>Tens and tens of author that remained in the shaddow of an apparent successfull story. It is too easy now to forget that and claim we suddenly understand and make hundreds of book repeating that. The interesting question is why people fail to respond and move on and not pretend there is a sudden switch of social pattern or a new trend.</p>
<p>I am french, and i can cite Simone Weill that before ww2 sayed that all industrial states, communist or capitalist are running on emptiness. Everybody was laughing at those statement because the power was in the hand of those who used coal and oil. People follow powers.</p>
<p>Those people that made these deep criticisms decades ago were all critics of civilisation in some way. </p>
<p>And the true question is &#8220;Should we save civilization&#8221; or should we fight this social pattern fiercely because it is intrinsically failing and give space to new way for human to relate to each other. Not based on book, trends, chiefs, leaders, organisation, but on free critical intelligent individuals.</p>
<p>I can only recommend all peak oil readers to read about the civilisatioin critics, if they never heard about this.</p>
<p>Because a transition to the same social pattern can be the sure way to fail.</p>
